annotation: Springsteen attends a show by the Ramones. Although he doesn’t join them onstage he spends some time with the group backstage, apparently sitting and harmonizing a few songs with Joey Ramone, who half-jokingly asks Bruce to write them a song – Bruce goes home that evening and begins to write what turns out to be “Hungry Heart”, although he ultimately decides (upon recommendation of Jon Landau) to keep the song for his own use.

name: KISS at River Trails Middle School Gymnasium
annotation: This concert was held as part of a contest held by the Mars candy company. Schools around the country collected as many Mars candy wrappers as they could, and the winner would get to host their own private KISS concert. The winning school was River Trails Middle School in Mount Prospect, Illinois, and this concert was held in the school's gymnasium.

disambiguation: Max and Becky Weinberg wedding reception
name: 1981‐06‐22: Private Residence, East Orange, NJ, USA
setlist: @ [70248960-cb53-4ea4-943a-edb18f7d336f|Bruce Springsteen]# &@ [d6652e7b-33fe-49ef-8336-4c863b4f996f|The E Street Band]* [dd21710e-a51b-3029-ae58-cd6a3559af26|You Can Look (but You Better Not Touch)]* [db8f3060-b101-3877-9805-ce054f923302|Hungry Heart]* [838be5c4-ce34-40ac-9f99-e78e35a7dede|Here She Comes]* [8c806b4e-edb4-3101-bc58-2605ec309a2e|Jersey Girl]# Incomplete setlist; “I Wanna Marry You” was likely performed among others.
annotation: Other set details unknown. The wedding reception for [https://musicbrainz.org/artist/2566ca73-1dfd-49e7-ab20-dfa5697b360e|Max Weinberg] and his bride [https://musicbrainz.org/artist/01c7aec0-21f3-4ae1-a757-f32be9e365ba|Rebecca (Becky)]. [https://musicbrainz.org/artist/70248960-cb53-4ea4-943a-edb18f7d336f|Bruce] and the entire [https://musicbrainz.org/artist/d6652e7b-33fe-49ef-8336-4c863b4f996f|E Street Band] attended and played a lengthy set. A source recalls that one of the songs Springsteen performed was [https://musicbrainz.org/work/8c806b4e-edb4-3101-bc58-2605ec309a2e|Jersey Girl] (very plausible, as Bruce premiered a cover version at his next public concert). From the clips that are available, [https://musicbrainz.org/work/dd21710e-a51b-3029-ae58-cd6a3559af26|You Can Look (but You Better Not Touch)], [https://musicbrainz.org/work/db8f3060-b101-3877-9805-ce054f923302|Hungry Heart], and [https://musicbrainz.org/work/c19036a4-5f3f-42ea-9646-54a31401c797|Here She Comes Walkin’] are also known to have been played. It seems likely that [https://musicbrainz.org/work/d771b3f7-38d2-3a7d-98b0-ee76403fceea|I Wanna Marry You] followed the latter (a short clip of which can be seen in [https://musicbrainz.org/artist/eea2b7c6-443c-49ae-8643-1210ccac6831|Thom Zimny]’s documentary [https://musicbrainz.org/release/f8da1af3-081b-4c1f-8179-8d22b6c6cbbf|The Ties That Bind]), but we have no evidence to confirm it.

name: 1981‐09‐24: Private Residence, Honolulu, HI, USA
setlist: @ [70248960-cb53-4ea4-943a-edb18f7d336f|Bruce Springsteen]# with@ [d6652e7b-33fe-49ef-8336-4c863b4f996f|The E Street Band]# No set details known
annotation: Wedding reception for the [https://musicbrainz.org/artist/7e4bfa5f-a8b8-4fb0-81b5-f74f6ac72133|Big Man] and his bride, “Christina Sandgren”. The entire [https://musicbrainz.org/artist/d6652e7b-33fe-49ef-8336-4c863b4f996f|E Street Band], key management and respective wives/girlfriends attended, as well as [https://musicbrainz.org/artist/70248960-cb53-4ea4-943a-edb18f7d336f|Bruce] and his then-girlfriend “Joyce Hyser”. Springsteen acted as “Best Man”. As had been the case at [https://musicbrainz.org/artist/2566ca73-1dfd-49e7-ab20-dfa5697b360e|Max Weinberg]'s wedding three months earlier, Bruce & The E Street Band performed a lengthy, rollicking set at the reception, all of which was audio and video recorded – but none of which has surfaced to collectors. This event (albeit a private and unofficial one) remains the only known Springsteen performance in the state of [https://musicbrainz.org/area/1b420c08-51a5-4bdd-9b0e-cd601703d20b|Hawaii].

annotation: Wedding reception for [https://musicbrainz.org/artist/f826b4d1-2dc3-4c4f-ba70-69b472320338|Southside Johnny] and his bride, “Jill Glasner”. The newly-formed 1982 lineup of “The Asbury Jukes” (with former [https://musicbrainz.org/artist/d6652e7b-33fe-49ef-8336-4c863b4f996f|E Street Band] member [https://musicbrainz.org/artist/2549e110-9933-4331-bd8d-a632f0cd639c|Ernest “Boom” Carter] on drums) provided the musical entertainment at the reception, along with “special guest” [https://musicbrainz.org/artist/70248960-cb53-4ea4-943a-edb18f7d336f|Bruce Springsteen]. Most E Street Band and Asbury Jukes members (past and present) were in attendance.
